<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Shell relatively large, brownish with a small, somewhat lighter girdle at the periphery, sculptured with incrassate growth striae and spiral striation, most noteable on the upper whorls, suture slightly ascending in front, peristome thin, sinuous, simple.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Dimensions.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Shell height 78.0, diameter 36.0 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
